This paper deals with the optimization of cell association in 5G systems, which involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers the available backhaul capacity, which is related to information theory and coding, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper proposes a novel association algorithm that takes into account the cell-load, which is a system-level aspect, indicating cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the third likely category. The paper uses simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithm, which involves data analysis and visualization, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of power control settings, which is related to cryptography and security, indicating cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the fifth likely category.
